4 This was our first trip to Flemings and this was our annual family Christmas dinner.  Our first impression was "wow" this place is beautiful.. dark woods, cozy booths, nice bar area.  We were pleasantly greeted and promptly seated.  Our server was equally prompt at greeting us and introducing herself.    Even though this was a busy Saturday night, we were not rushed or hurried in any way.  The ambiance is very relaxing and conducive to conversation.  All of us, except one, ordered a steak and the odd man out had the scallops.  Two ordered French Onion soup, three ordered the Wedge salad with bleu cheese.  All of our  meals were prepared to perfect order and the steaks were all prepared perfectly (3 small Filet Mignons and 1 New York).  All of the steaks were very flavorful and the New York was exceptional.  The side dish of Fleming Potatoes was also excellent!  The scallops were moist and also prepared perfectly with a beautiful sauce.    Through all of this, our server remained attentive,  yet not intrusive.  We finished our meal with a capuccino that was very good, but somewhat too cool.  The wine list is extensive with many good selections, all be it,, a tad expensive.    Overall, Flemings has won us over and we will certainly return.  With many outstanding steak houses in Las Vegas, this ranks right up at the top of the list.  Definitely a place to go for a special occassion!
2 Craving steaks & didn't feel like driving to the strip so we drove down the street to Fleming's.   I've always loved their abundant wine-by-the-glass menu since my wife doesn't drink and a full bottle by myself would be excessive.    We started with crab cakes and calamari...both recommendations from our server.  Crab cakes were decent.  Calamari was inedible as it was drowned in a sweet & sour sauce.  We mentioned it to our server who casually apologized.  One of my kids ordered the filet prix fix which was quite delicious.  3 fat cubes of filet on a skewer on a bed of mashed potatoes.  $50 was a good value.  We ordered his medium since he's only 8, but it came medium rare which is better than overcooking.    My other younger kid ordered the side of mac & cheese which was really good.  My wife's osao bucco was overcooked and charred.  Inedible.  My rib-eye was about super thin and dry.  I asked for it med-rare but it came med-well.  Inedible.  The worst part of the meal is that it took 45 min between apps and the entree.  We kept asking our server when the entrees were coming bcuz our kids were starving.  For about 15 min, we didn't even see our server so we just flagged down anybody.  Apparently they had a big holiday party in their banquet room.  I'm sure their food was cooked to the temp requested.  Do yourself a favor...drive to the strip, deal with the tourist traffic, do some fun people-watching, and go to a steakhouse that knows how to cook a steak properly.  I think that is the #1 prerequisite if "steakhouse" is in your name...get the temperature right in the meat!!
5 I am a big fan of Fleming's and make a special trip out to this particular location whenever I am in Las Vegas. It is a considerable distance from the strip but well worth the trip, especially for the happy hour. Happy hour is from 5pm-7pm 7 days a week. There are five wines, five martinis (with premium liquor,) 5 appetizers, and the prime burger with cheese and bacon for a mere $6 each.  I have been to this Fleming's several times and have always sat at the bar. The service is always excellent and the food and drink quality is top notch. Here is what we ordered:  Appletinis - the drinks are strong without being too boozy tasting, and thankfully they are not cloyingly sweet like some flavored martinis. The appletini is made with Grey Goose ($6)  White cosmos - Ketel One, peach schnapps, white cranberry juice, and lime juice garnished with dried blueberries. This drink is light and fruity with a nice fragrant sweetness ($6)  There were 4 of us and we had prime burgers all around, and at $6 each these are quite the bargain! It is a huge burger with your choice of cheese (2 of us had bleu cheese the other 2 had swiss,) and alot of bacon, served with onion rings or fries. We all ordered the burgers medium rare and they were perfectly cooked, juicy, and delicious.  Seared ahi tuna - lightly seared but served cold with a spicy mustard sauce. Quoting one of my dining partners, "This is amazing. I could eat this all day, every day."  Beef carpaccio - paper thin slices of heavenly raw beef filet served with a creamy creole mustard sauce and cheesy toast. OMG is all I can say. I have this every time I am in a Fleming's and it is always amazing.  We could not resist ordering dessert and had 2 delicious creme brulees. The best part of the desserts at Fleming's is that they are served with a bowl (or a trough if you ask nicely) of fluffy and decadent chantilly cream. While quite amazing we pretty much abandoned the creme brulee and started eating the chantilly cream out of the trough with our spoons while making loud "nom, nom, nom" sounds.  Other items on the  $6 happy hour menu:  APPETIZERS: SWEET CHILI CALAMARI WICKED CAJUN BARBECUE SHRIMP JUMBO LUMP CRAB CAKES, Red Pepper Sauce   COCKTAILS: FLEMING'S CLASSIC, Ketel One Vodka MARGATINI, Gran Centenario Anejo Tequila TROPICAL MARTINI, Malibu Coconut Rum  5 WINES BY THE GLASS: PINOT GRIGIO, Redbank, Australia CHARDONNAY, Glen Carlou, South Africa PINOT NOIR, Mark West, California PETITE SIRAH, Vinum, California CABERNET SAUVIGNON, 14 Hands, Washington   As I mentioned earlier the service was excellent. Our bartender was alone behind the bar yet was able to give great service and make great drinks for us while also producing cocktails for a very crowded bar and dining room. Her bright and sincere smile never left her lips and our glasses were never dry. As soon as our glasses were half empty she asked if we needed more cocktails. We didn't have to wait very long for anything. Our food came out of the kitchen amazingly fast and at the correct temperature. The service was extraordinary from the time the door was opened for us and we were greeted by the hostess until the time we were sincerely thanked and wished a good evening, and again had the door opened for us by the hostess. Fleming's is the perfect example of great food and great customer service, and this particular location does not disappoint.
