4 Happy Hour is until 7pm and it is a great value for good food and wine. The bar is not big enough for socializing, but if you're looking for quality food at a good price in a more upscale environment, this is the place.
4 One of my favorite happy hour spots!  I've been here for dinner and it's pretty good but in Vegas, there's probably at least another 30 steakhouses you can go to.   What differentates this steakhouse for me is the value of their happy hour.  This place sh1ts all over Kona Grill's happy hour.  We had each of the 5 appeteizers offered:  Tenderloin Carpaccio, Sweet Chili Calamari, Seared Ahi Tuna, Cajun BBQ Shrimp, and a Mushroom Ravioli.  They also offer wine by the glass and cocktails.  Every item is 6 bucks which makes it affordable to hit this spot frequently.  The only downside is in terms of food, there's only 5 items and i'm not sure how often it rotates.  Also, it's only served in bar till 7pm.    BUt still, for the value and quality of food for 6 bucks an appeteizer, you can't beat it.
